Q10. What is a .gitignore file? Write a .gitignore for an Arduino project that excludes compiled output files (.hex, .elf), OS-specific files (.DS_Store, Thumbs.db), 
and IDE configuration folders (.vscode/, build/).



Answer -

.gitignore file is used to specify files and folders that Git should ignore and not track in the repository.
It helps keep the repository clean by excluding generated files, temporary files, compiled outputs, operating system files, and IDE-specific configuration files.

project -
# Compiled output files
*.hex
*.elf

# Build directory
build/

# VS Code settings
.vscode/

# OS-specific files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
